'''斯蒂芬·蒂龙·科拜尔'''（{{lang-en|Stephen Tyrone Colbert}}，{{IPAc-en|k|oʊ|l|ˈ|b|ɛər}}，原为{{IPAc-en|ˈ|k|oʊ|l|b|ər|t}}（科尔伯特），{{bd|1964年|5月13日|||catIdx=Colbert, Stephen}}）中国大陆常译为'''扣扣熊'''，是一位[[美国|美国]]的电视节目[[主持人|主持人]]和[[喜剧|喜剧]]演员，[[艾美奖|艾美奖]]获得者。因其[[讽刺|讽刺]]和[[扑克|扑克]]脸式的喜剧表演风格在美国广为人知，主持[[喜劇中心|喜剧中心]]频道[[讽刺|讽刺]]新闻节目[[科拜尔报告|科拜尔报告]]，科拜尔在节目中扮演[[保守派|保守派]][[政治|政治]][[评论家|评论家]]。2015年9月8日，科拜尔接替[[大卫·莱特曼|大卫·莱特曼]]接手[[哥伦比亚广播公司|哥伦比亚广播公司]]旗下深夜节目時段《[[荷伯報到|史蒂芬·柯貝爾晚間秀]]》。<ref name="lateshow">{{cite web |url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2014/04/10/stephen-colbert-taking-over-david-lettermans-late-night-spot/ |title=Stephen Colbert Leaving Character Behind To Take Over David Letterman's Late-Night Spot |work=[[Forbes|Forbes]] |date=April 10, 2014 |accessdate=April 10, 2014 |archive-date=2014-04-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411213314/http://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2014/04/10/stephen-colbert-taking-over-david-lettermans-late-night-spot/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

科拜尔原本准备读书成为[[戏剧|戏剧]]演员，但他在[[西北大学_(伊利诺伊州)|西北大学]]读书时对即兴戏剧产生了兴趣，并在学校认识了[[第二城喜剧团|第二城喜剧团]]的主管德尔·克洛斯。科拜尔第一次作为[[史提夫·加維|史蒂夫·卡瑞尔]]的替身在第二城演出，他的剧团伙伴包括保罗·迪内罗和艾米·塞达里斯，这些喜剧演员与他一起开发了小品喜剧系列《出口57》（Exit 57）。在拍摄邪典电视连续剧《带着糖果的陌生人》（Strangers with Candy）之前，科拜尔在昙花一现的达娜·卡维秀中创作并出演。他因在后者中饰演出柜的同性恋历史教师查克·诺布莱特而获得关注。

科拜尔在[[喜劇中心|喜剧中心]]的新闻模仿系列剧《[[每日秀|每日秀]]》中担任记者，获得了广泛的认可。2005年，他离开《每日秀》，主持《[[科拜尔报告|科拜尔报告]]》。秉承《每日秀》的新闻模仿概念，《科拜尔报告》是对《奥莱利因素》为主的由主持人个性和个人观点驱动的[[時事評論員|政治评论]]节目的讽刺，他在节目中扮演了一个可笑的的“保守派政治专家”。该系列节目成为喜剧中心收视率最高的系列节目之一，为科拜尔赢得了2006年在[[白宮記者協會|白宫记者协会晚宴]]上作为特邀艺人表演的邀请。结束《科尔伯特报告》后，他于2015年受聘接替退休的[[大卫·莱特曼|大卫·莱特曼]]成为[[CBS_(電視網)|CBS]][[晚间秀|晚间秀]]的主持人。2017年9月，他主持了第69届[[艾美奖|艾美奖]]颁奖典礼。

科拜尔曾获得9次[[艾美奖|艾美奖]]、2次[[葛萊美獎|格莱美奖]]和2次[[皮博迪獎|皮博迪奖]]。科拜尔在2006年和2012年被评为《[[時代雜誌|时代周刊]]》100位最具影响力的人物之一<ref name="time1002">{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,1975813_1975838_1976306,00.html|title=Stephen Colbert – The 2006 TIME 100|last=Williams|first=Brian|work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|date=May 8, 2006|access-date=July 25, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120724022225/http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0%2C28804%2C1975813_1975838_1976306%2C00.html|archivedate=July 24, 2012}}</ref><ref name="time100-12">{{cite news|url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2111975_2111976_2111953,00.html|title=Stephen Colbert – 2012 TIME 100: The Most Influential People in the World|last=Trudeau|first=Garry|work=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|date=April 16, 2012|access-date=July 25, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120725101401/http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0%2C28804%2C2111975_2111976_2111953%2C00.html|archivedate=July 25, 2012}}</ref>。科拜尔的书《我是美国（你也可以！）》在2007年被列为《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》畅销书排行榜第一名。

== 簡介 ==
科拜尔从[[西北大学_(伊利诺伊州)|西北大学]]毕业之后就从事表演工作。1997年，他加入了美国[[喜劇中心|喜劇中心]]电视台的时政节目《[[乔恩·斯图尔特|乔恩·斯图尔特]][[每日秀|每日秀]]》（The Daily Show with Jon Stewart）。在节目中，他扮演了一个虚构的[[记者|记者]]角色，他自己称之为“意图明确却知之甚少的高级白痴”。

2005年，他开始主持同一所电视台的另一个节目——《[[科拜尔报告|科拜尔报告]]》。该节目是从《[[乔恩·斯图尔特|乔恩·斯图尔特]][[每日秀|每日秀]]》衍生出来的。在节目中，科拜尔通过[[戏仿|戏仿]][[右翼|右翼]]人士——尤其是美国[[福克斯电视台|福克斯电视台]]的一些时政节目主持人——的方式达到讽刺的目的。

2006年4月29日，科拜尔受邀在白宫新闻记者协会晚餐会上进行表演。科拜尔用他一贯的风格当面挖苦了[[美国总统|美国总统]][[乔治·W·布什|乔治·W·布什]]，这段长达24分钟的表演让他在互联网上轰动起来，2006年和2012年科拜尔被[[时代杂志|时代杂志]]评为100个最有影响力的人之一。<ref name="time100">{{cite news|url = http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,1975813_1975838_1976306,00.html|title = Stephen Colbert - The 2006 TIME 100 - TIME|author = Brian Williams|publisher = ''[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]''|date = May 8, 2006|accessdate = July 25, 2012|archive-date = 2012-07-24|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120724022225/http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0%2C28804%2C1975813_1975838_1976306%2C00.html|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref name="time100-1">{{cite news|url = http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2111975_2111976_2111953,00.html|title = Stephen Colbert - 2012 TIME 100: The Most Influential People in the World - TIME|author = Garry Trudeau|publisher = ''[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]''|date = April 16, 2012|accessdate = July 25, 2012|archive-date = 2012-07-25|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120725101401/http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0%2C28804%2C2111975_2111976_2111953%2C00.html|dead-url = no}}</ref>

== 早期生涯 ==
斯蒂芬·科拜尔出生于[[华盛顿哥伦比亚特区|华盛顿特区]]<ref name="dowd" /><ref name="alum">{{cite news|title=A Funny Man of Good Report|work=Northwestern Magazine|first=Marley|last=Seaman|date=Winter 2005|url=http://www.northwestern.edu/magazine/winter2005/alumninews/close-ups/colbert.html|access-date=July 11, 2007|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070714022233/http://www.northwestern.edu/magazine/winter2005/alumninews/close-ups/colbert.html|archivedate=July 14, 2007}}</ref>，他是[[天主教|天主教]]家庭里11个孩子中最小的一个<ref name="charlestonian">{{cite news|last1=Donovan|first1=Bryce|title=Great Charlestonian?{{nbsp}}... Or the Greatest Charlestonian?|url=http://colbertsheroes.org/articles/CharlestonPost-Apr29-06.shtml|accessdate=20 August 2020|work=[[The_Post_and_Courier|The Post and Courier]]|publisher=[[Evening_Post_Industries|Evening Post Industries]]|date=April 29, 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070108132259/http://www.colbertsheroes.org/articles/CharlestonPost-Apr29-06.shtml|archivedate=January 8, 2007|location=[[Charleston,_South_Carolina|Charleston, South Carolina]]|language=en}}<!-- The original link for this piece appears to have been at http://www.charleston.net/stories/?newsID=83674 but was not archived in the Internet Archive. I fear that someone may need to check a paper copy for accuracy. (Reach Prentiss Findlay to investigate at ph:XXX-XXXX via https://www.postandcourier.com/archives/cbs-picks-charlestons-stephen-colbert-to-succeed-letterman-on-late-show/article_94a5b228-bef1-5c50-8f70-b2e0545bb829.html) (written for White House Correspondents' Dinner, April 29, 2006) --></ref><ref name="25questions">{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/25/magazine/25questions.html|title=Funny About the News|first=Deborah|last=Solomon|work=The New York Times|date=September 25, 2005|access-date=July 22, 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111026021336/http://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/25/magazine/25questions.html|archivedate=October 26, 2011}}</ref>。他早年在[[马里兰州|马里兰州]][[贝塞斯达_(马里兰州)|贝塞斯达]]度过<ref>King, Larry. "Interview with Stephen Colbert". ''Larry King Live''. CNN. October 14, 2007.</ref>，在[[南卡罗来纳州|南卡罗来纳州]][[詹姆斯岛|詹姆斯岛]]的[[查尔斯顿_(南卡罗来纳州)|查尔斯顿]]郊区长大。科拜尔和他的兄弟姐妹，按年龄递减顺序分别是詹姆斯三世、爱德华、玛丽、威廉、马戈、托马斯、杰伊、伊丽莎白、保罗、彼得和斯蒂芬。他的父亲小詹姆斯·威廉·科尔伯特是[[免疫学|免疫学家]]，曾在[[耶鲁大学|耶鲁大学]]、[[圣路易斯大学|圣路易斯大学]]担任[[醫學院|医学院]]院长，最后在南卡罗来纳医科大学担任院长，从1969年开始，他担任该校第一任学术事务副校长<ref name="PnC-Late-Show-debut">{{cite web|title=Stephen Colbert's debut on 'Late Show' signals triumph for Charleston, state|url=https://www.postandcourier.com/archives/stephen-colbert-s-debut-on-late-show-signals-triumph-for-charleston-state/article_9c61ff35-f175-505e-b812-3cb71a1b6089.html|accessdate=20 August 2020|date=September 4, 2015|publisher=[[Evening_Post_Industries|Evening Post Industries]]|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20200820015949/https://www.postandcourier.com/archives/stephen-colbert-s-debut-on-late-show-signals-triumph-for-charleston-state/article_9c61ff35-f175-505e-b812-3cb71a1b6089.html|archivedate=2020-08-20|quote=Colbert told ''The Post and Courier'' in a 2006 interview that he “kind of just shut off” after that. He turned to science fiction novels, consuming one a day for eight years.|last1=Darlington|first1=Abigail|website=[[The_Post_and_Courier|The Post and Courier]]|location=[[Charleston,_South_Carolina|Charleston, South Carolina]]}}<!-- ??? https://www.postandcourier.com/archives/stephen-colbert/article_cdd4d1ea-5596-51e3-9c75-1890712acc9c.html --></ref>。 斯蒂芬的母亲洛娜·伊丽莎白·科尔伯特（née Tuck）是一位家庭主妇<ref name="Faces" /><ref name="web2">{{cite web|title=Family & Education|url=http://www.library.musc.edu/exhibits/colbert/EarlyYears.php|year=2009|publisher=Medical University of South Carolina Library|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100317083210/http://www.library.musc.edu/exhibits/colbert/EarlyYears.php|archivedate=March 17, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|title=Stephen Colbert's Mother Dies at 92|url=https://people.com/celebrity/stephen-colberts-mom-dead-lorna-elizabeth-tuck-colbert-was-92/|magazine=[[People_(magazine)|People]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150522112104/http://www.people.com/people/article/0%2C%2C20709467%2C00.html|archivedate=May 22, 2015}}</ref>。

在采访中，科拜尔曾描述他的父母是虔诚的人，他们也非常重视[[主知主義|主知主义]]，并教导他们的孩子可以质疑教会，但仍然是天主教徒<ref name="TimeOut">{{cite magazine|last=Cote|first=David|date=June 9, 2005|title=Joyce Words|url=https://www.timeout.com/newyork/DetailsAr.do?file=hotseat/506/506.hotseat.html|magazine=[[Time_Out_New_York|Time Out New York]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060820014908/http://www.timeout.com/newyork/DetailsAr.do?file=hotseat%2F506%2F506.hotseat.html|archivedate=August 20, 2006|access-date=July 30, 2008}} Via the [[Internet_Archive|Internet Archive]].</ref>。在一次采访中，洛娜曾描述科拜尔是一个漫不经心的人<ref>{{cite web|title=Stephen Colbert: His SC connections through the years|url=https://www.thestate.com/living/article13847510.html|accessdate=21 August 2020|date=April 12, 2014|publisher=[[The_McClatchy_Company|The McClatchy Company]]|website=[[The_State_(newspaper)|The State]]|location=Columbia, South Carolina|archive-date=2018-03-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180329153525/http://www.thestate.com/living/article13847510.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。作为一个孩子，他观察到[[美國南部|南方人]]经常被描述为不如其他电视剧本中的角色聪明；为了避免这种[[刻板印象|刻板印象]]，他自学模仿美国[[新聞主播|新闻主播]]的讲话方式<ref name="freshair1">{{cite interview|url=https://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4464017|title=A Fake Newsman's Fake Newsman: Stephen Colbert|first=Stephen|last=Colbert|interviewer=Terry Gross|work=Fresh Air|publisher=[[NPR|NPR]]|date=January 24, 2005|access-date=21 April 2020|archive-date=2007-07-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070701141740/http://www.npr.org/templates/story/story.php?storyId=4464017|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="60minutes">{{cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2006/04/27/60minutes/main1553506.shtml|title=The Colbert Report: Morley Safer Profiles Comedy Central's 'Fake' Newsman|first=Morley|last=Safer|authorlink=Morley Safer|series=[[60_Minutes|60 Minutes]]|date=August 13, 2006|access-date=August 15, 2006|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060820141728/http://www.cbsnews.com/stories/2006/04/27/60minutes/main1553506.shtml|archivedate=August 20, 2006}}</ref>。

虽然科拜尔有时滑稽地声称他的姓氏源自[[法国|法国]]，他是15到16分之一的[[爱尔兰人|爱尔兰人]]；他的一位父辈[[曾祖父母|曾曾祖母]]是[[德国|德国]]和[[英国|英国]]后裔<ref>Smolenyak, Megan. {{cite news|url=http://irishamerica.com/2015/01/stephen-colbert-one-last-report-its-genealogical|title=Stephen Colbert: One Last Report (It's Genealogical)|work=Irish America Magazine|access-date=March 26, 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150317031748/http://irishamerica.com/2015/01/stephen-colbert-one-last-report-its-genealogical/|archivedate=March 17, 2015}}</ref><ref name="gatesref">{{cite news|last=Gagnon|first=Geoffrey|title=Top of Mind: Extended Q & A with Henry Louis Gates Jr.|work=Boston|year=2010|url=http://www.bostonmagazine.com/articles/skipgates/page2|access-date=February 4, 2010|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120229050129/http://www.bostonmagazine.com/articles/skipgates/page2|archivedate=February 29, 2012}}</ref>。他的许多祖先在[[爱尔兰大饥荒|19世纪大饥荒]]之前和期间从[[爱尔兰|爱尔兰]]移民到北美。<ref name="Faces">[https://www.pbs.org/wnet/facesofamerica/profiles/stephen-colbert/11/ "Faces of America: Stephen Colbert"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100310164800/http://www.pbs.org/wnet/facesofamerica/profiles/stephen-colbert/11/|date=March 10, 2010}}, PBS, ''[[Faces_of_America_(PBS_series)|Faces of America]]'' series, with Professor [[Henry_Louis_Gates|Henry Louis Gates, Jr.]] (2010).</ref><ref name="Pedigree">[http://colbert.ancestortree.net/pedigree.php "Pedigree of Stephen Colbert"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170214231610/http://colbert.ancestortree.net/pedigree.php|date=February 14, 2017}}, AncestorTree.net; retrieved August 29, 2010.</ref>最初，他的姓氏在英语中发音为科尔伯特（{{IPAc-en|ˈ|k|oʊ|l|b|ər|t}} KOHL-bərt）；科拜尔的父亲詹姆斯想把名字念成科拜尔（{{IPAc-en|k|oʊ|l|ˈ|b|ɛər}} kohl-AIR），但出于对自己父亲的尊重，维持了科尔伯特的发音。他为他的孩子们提供了选择，他们可以遵循自己喜欢的发音<ref name="charlestonian" />。斯蒂芬·科拜尔在青少年时代后期才选择使用科拜尔：在转学到[[西北大学_(伊利诺伊州)|西北大学]]时他利用在一个新的地方，没人知道自己的机会下重塑自己的形象<ref name="dowd" />。斯蒂芬的哥哥爱德华，[[知识产权|知识产权]][[律師|律师]]，则保留了科尔伯特；在2009年2月12日，在科拜尔报告出场时，当斯蒂芬问他，"科尔伯特或科拜尔？"时爱德华回答说："科尔伯特"，斯蒂芬则开玩笑地回答说："那我们地狱里见"<ref>{{cite web|title=Obama Poster Debate – David Ross and Ed Colbert|url=http://www.cc.com/video-clips/f0688o/the-colbert-report-obama-poster-debate---david-ross-and-ed-colbert|date=February 12, 2009|publisher=[[The_Colbert_Report|The Colbert Report]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150914000441/http://www.cc.com/video-clips/f0688o/the-colbert-report-obama-poster-debate---david-ross-and-ed-colbert|archivedate=September 14, 2015|access-date=February 15, 2009}}</ref>。

1974年9月11日，当科拜尔10岁时，他的父亲和年龄最近的两个兄弟彼得和保罗在[[東方航空_(美國)|东方航空公司]]212号航班试图降落在[[北卡罗来纳州|北卡罗来纳州]][[夏洛特_(北卡羅來納州)|夏洛特]]空难中逝世<ref name="JetCrash-Florence">{{cite news|title=Fiery Charlotte Jet Crash Kills Sixty Nine Persons|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150329172250/http://www3.gendisasters.com/north-carolina/3843/charlotte%2C-nc-jet-crash-kills-sixty-nine%2C-sep-1974|accessdate=20 August 2020|work=Morning News|via=GenDisasters.com|date=September 12, 1974|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150329172250/http://www3.gendisasters.com/north-carolina/3843/charlotte%2C-nc-jet-crash-kills-sixty-nine%2C-sep-1974|archivedate=March 29, 2015|location=Florence, South Carolina}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/stephen-colbert-bio-2015-9/#colbert-was-raised-catholic-to-this-day-he-is-a-dedicated-churchgoer-3|title=How Stephen Colbert endured tragedy and became one of the greatest political satirists of our time|work=Business Insider|access-date=October 12, 2017|archive-date=2019-04-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190413043444/https://www.businessinsider.com/stephen-colbert-bio-2015-9#colbert-was-raised-catholic-to-this-day-he-is-a-dedicated-churchgoer-3|dead-url=no}}</ref>，他们当时正在去[[康乃狄克州|康涅狄格州]][[新米爾福德_(康乃狄克州)|新米尔福德]]坎特伯雷学校给两个男孩报名的途中<ref name="25questions" /><ref name="obit2">{{cite news|title=Obituaries|work=The Washington Post|date=September 14, 1974}}</ref> 。科拜尔曾讨论过对他的影响以及他的悲伤和痛苦哲学<ref>{{cite web|title=Stephen Colbert and Anderson Cooper's beautiful conversation about grief|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YB46h1koicQ|accessdate=22 September 2019|date=17 August 2019|publisher=CNN|website=YouTube.com|archive-date=2021-03-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210324052612/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YB46h1koicQ|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Tragic Plane Crash That Changed Stephen Colbert Season 2 Episode 202|url=http://www.oprah.com/own-oprahs-next-chapter/The-Tragic-Plane-Crash-That-Changed-Stephen-Colbert-Video#ixzz3lZTKha14|accessdate=22 September 2019|date=30 September 2012|publisher=Oprah Winfrey|website=Oprah.com|archive-date=2021-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210203104631/https://www.oprah.com/own-oprahs-next-chapter/the-tragic-plane-crash-that-changed-stephen-colbert-video#ixzz3lZTKha14|dead-url=no}}</ref>。事件后洛娜将全家从詹姆斯岛搬到了[[查尔斯顿_(南卡罗来纳州)|查尔斯顿]]市中心，并将佣人房作为民宿来经营<ref name="Aldridge-Bio">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lJthDwAAQBAJ&q=%22carriage+house%22&pg=PA32|last1=Aldridge|first1=Rebecca|title=Stephen Colbert|date=December 15, 2015|publisher=[[The_Rosen_Publishing_Group,_Inc.|The Rosen Publishing Group, Inc.]]|isbn=978-1-4994-6260-9|page=32|language=en|quote=Lorna hadn't remarried, and she was running a bed-and-breakfast out of a carriage house.}}</ref><ref name="Colbert-BnB-Island">{{cite web|title=Stephen Colbert's Favorite Things to Do in Charleston|url=https://www.travelandleisure.com/travel-tips/celebrity-travel/stephen-colberts-favorite-things-to-do-in-charleston|accessdate=20 August 2020|date=May 14, 2014|publisher=[[Meredith_Corporation|Meredith Corporation]]|language=EN|quote=Back then, if I booked a guest, I got ten percent. A kid could have a whole weekend of fun on fifteen bucks......We’d go swimming off Sullivan’s Island<!-- (What cost $15 in 1975 would cost $72.28 in 2019.) -->|last1=Austin|first1=Tom|website=[[Travel_+_Leisure|Travel + Leisure]]|archive-date=2020-11-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125202348/https://www.travelandleisure.com/travel-tips/celebrity-travel/stephen-colberts-favorite-things-to-do-in-charleston|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=39 East Bay Street (George Chisolm House)|url=https://charleston.pastperfectonline.com/archive/5897F7F8-D852-46B1-B126-481381463030|accessdate=20 August 2020|publisher=Margaretta Childs Archives|website=Historic Charleston Foundation}}</ref>。科拜尔发现很难适应新生活，在新的社区里不容易交到朋友<ref name="charlestonian" />。科拜尔后来形容自己在这段时间里对事物是疏离的，对于其他孩子关心的事情缺乏重视感<ref name="60minutes" /><ref name="ign">{{cite web|title=An Interview with Stephen Colbert|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2003/08/11/an-interview-with-stephen-colbert|date=August 11, 2003|last=P.|first=Ken|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105202148/http://www.ign.com/articles/2003/08/11/an-interview-with-stephen-colbert|archivedate=January 5, 2014|website=IGN|access-date=July 22, 2006}}</ref> 。

他对[[科幻小说|科幻小说]]和[[奇幻文學|奇幻小说]]情有独钟，尤其是[[J·R·R·托爾金|J.R.R.托尔金]]的作品，他至今仍是其狂热粉丝。在青少年时期，他还对奇幻[[角色扮演游戏|角色扮演]]游戏产生了浓厚的兴趣，尤其是《[[龙与地下城|龙与地下城]]》<ref name="ign" /><ref name="gamespy">{{cite web|title=Stephen Colbert on D&D|url=http://pc.gamespy.com/pc/dungeons-dragons-online/537989p1.html|date=August 17, 2004|last=Rausch|first=Allen|publisher=[[GameSpy|GameSpy]]|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060818143601/http://pc.gamespy.com/pc/dungeons-dragons-online/537989p1.html|archivedate=August 18, 2006|access-date=July 22, 2006}}</ref>，这种消遣活动后来被他定性为早期的表演和即兴表演经验。

科拜尔就读于[[查尔斯顿_(南卡罗来纳州)|查尔斯顿]]的主教波特·高德学校，在那里他参加了几个学校的戏剧表演，并为学校的报纸做出了贡献，但在学业上并没有很高的积极性<ref name="ign" />。 在青春期时，他曾短暂地担任滚石乐队翻唱乐队A Shot in the Dark的主唱<ref>{{cite news|last=Daly|first=Steven|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/3673509/Stephen-Colbert-the-second-most-powerful-idiot-in-America.html|title=Stephen Colbert: the second most powerful idiot in America|page=3|work=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|date=May 18, 2008|access-date=May 18, 2008|location=London|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090312075305/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/3673509/Stephen-Colbert-the-second-most-powerful-idiot-in-America.html|archivedate=March 12, 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Stephen Colbert's Most Meaningful Musical Moments|url=https://www.npr.org/2012/10/24/163547250/stephen-colberts-most-meaningful-musical-moments|publisher=NPR|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121025043934/http://www.npr.org/2012/10/24/163547250/stephen-colberts-most-meaningful-musical-moments|archivedate=October 25, 2012|series=Fresh Air|access-date=October 25, 2012}}</ref>。他年轻时曾想学习[[海洋生物学|海洋生物学]]，但修复严重穿孔的[[鼓膜|鼓膜]]的手术使他的[[內耳|内耳]]严重受损，足以排除任何需要[[潜水|潜水]]的职业，并使他的右耳[[听觉障碍|失聪]]。

有一段时间，科拜尔不确定自己是否会上大学<ref name="tiger">{{cite web|title=Student Meets Daily Show Correspondent With Ties to the Hill|url=http://www2.hsc.edu/news/archive/colbert.html|last=Beazley|first=Nick|year=2003|publisher=Hampden–Sydney College|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20031006095313/http://www.hsc.edu/news/archive/colbert.html|archivedate=October 6, 2003|website=The Hampden–Sydney Tiger}}</ref>，但他最终申请并被弗吉尼亚州的汉普顿·悉尼学院录取，他的朋友也在该校就读。1982年到校后，他主修哲学，并继续参加戏剧演出<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FktrNFjZfKg&t=1m35s Neil DeGrasse Tyson Interviews Stephen Colbert], Late Show (posted to YouTube on November 27, 2018) Quote:"When I was first in college I was a philosophy major{{nbsp}}..."</ref><ref name="ballots"></ref>Quote:"He studied philosophy in college."<ref>{{cite web|title=An Interview with Stephen Colbert|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2003/08/11/an-interview-with-stephen-colbert?page=2|date=August 11, 2003|last=P.|first=Ken|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140105202148/http://www.ign.com/articles/2003/08/11/an-interview-with-stephen-colbert|archivedate=January 5, 2014|website=IGN|access-date=July 22, 2006}}Quote:"Philosophy is what I took most classes in."</ref>，他觉得大学课程安排很严谨，但他比高中时更专注，能把自己的精力用到学习上。尽管汉普顿·悉尼缺乏重要的戏剧团体，但科拜尔对表演的兴趣在这段时间内不断升级。两年后，他于1984年转学到[[西北大学_(伊利诺伊州)|西北大学]]戏剧专业学习表演，他意识到自己喜欢表演，即使没有人来看演出，他也坚定了自己的信心<ref name="ign" />。1986年，科拜尔于西北大学传媒学院毕业<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2011-05-05/news/ct-talk-small-talk-0506-20110505_1_honorary-degree-baby-names-laura-wattenberg|title=Stephen Colbert to receive honorary degree from Northwestern University|newspaper=[[Chicago_Tribune|Chicago Tribune]]|date=May 5, 2011|access-date=November 29, 2015|author=Manker, Rob|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151208160833/http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2011-05-05/news/ct-talk-small-talk-0506-20110505_1_honorary-degree-baby-names-laura-wattenberg|archivedate=December 8, 2015}}</ref>。

